270 static int32_t CLI_MMWaveVersion (int32_t argc, char* argv[])
271 {
272  rlVersion_t verArgs;
273  int32_t retVal;
274  uint8_t rfPatchBuildVer, rfPatchDebugVer;
275  rlRfDieIdCfg_t dieId = { 0 };
276  SOC_PartNumber devicePartNumber;
277  uint8_t index;
278  int32_t errCode;
279 
280  /* print the platform */
281 #ifdef SOC_XWR14XX
282  CLI_write ("Platform : xWR14xx\n");
283 #elif defined(SOC_XWR16XX)
284  CLI_write ("Platform : xWR16xx\n");
285 #else
286  CLI_write ("Platform : unknown\n");
287 #endif
288 
289  /* Get the version string: */
290  retVal = SOC_getDevicePartNumber(gCLI.cfg.socHandle, &devicePartNumber, &errCode);
291  if (retVal < 0)
292  {
293  CLI_write ("Error: Unable to get the device version from SOC[Error %d]\n", errCode);
294  return -1;
295  }
296 
297  /* Get the version string: */
298  retVal = rlDeviceGetVersion(RL_DEVICE_MAP_INTERNAL_BSS, &verArgs);
299  if (retVal < 0)
300  {
301  CLI_write ("Error: Unable to get the device version from mmWave link [Error %d]\n", retVal);
302  return -1;
303  }
304 
305  /* Display the version information on the CLI Console: */
306  CLI_write ("mmWave SDK Version : %02d.%02d.%02d.%02d\n",
307  MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_MAJOR,
308  MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_MINOR,
309  MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_BUGFIX,
310  MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_BUILD);
311 
312  index = 0;
313  while(partInfoStringArray[index].partNumber !=0U)
314  {
315  if(devicePartNumber == partInfoStringArray[index].partNumber)
316  {
317  /* found device in supported list */
318  break;
319  }
320  index++;
321  }
322  if(partInfoStringArray[index].partNumber ==0U)
323  {
324  /* Device is not found in the list: */
325  CLI_write ("mmWave device [%2x] is not supported\n",
326  devicePartNumber);
327  }
328  else
329  {
330  /* Display the device information on the CLI Console: */
331  CLI_write ("Device Info : %s ES %02d.%02d\n",
332  partInfoStringArray[index].partNumString,verArgs.rf.hwMajor, verArgs.rf.hwMinor);
333  }
334 
335  CLI_write ("RF F/W Version : %02d.%02d.%02d.%02d.%02d.%02d.%02d\n",
336  verArgs.rf.fwMajor, verArgs.rf.fwMinor, verArgs.rf.fwBuild, verArgs.rf.fwDebug,
337  verArgs.rf.fwYear, verArgs.rf.fwMonth, verArgs.rf.fwDay);
338 
339  rfPatchDebugVer = ((verArgs.rf.patchBuildDebug) & 0x0F);
340  rfPatchBuildVer = (((verArgs.rf.patchBuildDebug) & 0xF0) >> 4);
341 
342  CLI_write ("RF F/W Patch : %02d.%02d.%02d.%02d.%02d.%02d.%02d\n",
343  verArgs.rf.patchMajor, verArgs.rf.patchMinor, rfPatchBuildVer, rfPatchDebugVer,
344  verArgs.rf.patchYear, verArgs.rf.patchMonth, verArgs.rf.patchDay);
345  CLI_write ("mmWaveLink Version : %02d.%02d.%02d.%02d\n",
346  verArgs.mmWaveLink.major, verArgs.mmWaveLink.minor,
347  verArgs.mmWaveLink.build, verArgs.mmWaveLink.debug);
348 
349  /* Get the die ID: */
350  retVal = rlGetRfDieId(RL_DEVICE_MAP_INTERNAL_BSS, &dieId);
351  if (retVal < 0)
352  {
353  CLI_write ("Error: Unable to get the device die ID from mmWave link [Error %d]\n", retVal);
354  return 0;
355  }
356 
357  CLI_write ("Lot number : %d\n", dieId.lotNo);
358  CLI_write ("Wafer number : %d\n", dieId.waferNo);
359  CLI_write ("Die coordinates in wafer: X = %d, Y = %d\n",
360  dieId.devX, dieId.devY);
361 
362  /* Version string has been formatted successfully. */
363  return 0;
364 }

383 static int32_t CLI_MMWaveFlushCfg (int32_t argc, char* argv[])
384 {
385  int32_t errCode;
386 
387  /* Flush the configuration in the MMWave */
388  if (MMWave_flushCfg (gCLI.cfg.mmWaveHandle, &errCode) < 0)
389  {
390  /* Error: Flushing the configuration failed. Return the error code back to the callee */
391  return errCode;
392  }
393 
394  /* Reset the global configuration: */
395  memset ((void*)&gCLIMMWaveControlCfg, 0, sizeof(MMWave_CtrlCfg));
396 
397  /* Reset the open configuration: */
398  memset ((void*)&gCLIMMWaveOpenCfg, 0, sizeof(MMWave_OpenCfg));
399  return 0;
400 }

419 static int32_t CLI_MMWaveDataOutputMode (int32_t argc, char* argv[])
420 {
421  uint32_t cfgMode;
422 
423  /* Sanity Check: Minimum argument check */
424  if (argc != 2)
425  {
426  CLI_write ("Error: Invalid usage of the CLI command\n");
427  return -1;
428  }
429 
430  /* Get the configuration mode: */
431  cfgMode = atoi (argv[1]);
432  switch (cfgMode)
433  {
434  case 1U:
435  {
436  gCLIMMWaveControlCfg.dfeDataOutputMode = MMWave_DFEDataOutputMode_FRAME;
437  break;
438  }
439  case 2U:
440  {
441  gCLIMMWaveControlCfg.dfeDataOutputMode = MMWave_DFEDataOutputMode_CONTINUOUS;
442  break;
443  }
444  case 3U:
445  {
446  gCLIMMWaveControlCfg.dfeDataOutputMode = MMWave_DFEDataOutputMode_ADVANCED_FRAME;
447  break;
448  }
449  default:
450  {
451  /* Error: Invalid argument. */
452  CLI_write ("Error: Invalid mode.\n");
453  return -1;
454  }
455  }
456 
457  return 0;
458 }

559 static int32_t CLI_MMWaveProfileCfg (int32_t argc, char* argv[])
560 {
561  rlProfileCfg_t profileCfg;
562  uint8_t index;
563  int32_t errCode;
564  MMWave_ProfileHandle profileHandle;
565  MMWave_ProfileHandle* ptrBaseCfgProfileHandle;
566 
567  /* Sanity Check: Minimum argument check */
568  if (argc != 15)
569  {
570  CLI_write ("Error: Invalid usage of the CLI command\n");
571  return -1;
572  }
573 
574  /* Sanity Check: Profile configuration is valid only for the Frame or
575  Advanced Frame Mode: */
576  if ((gCLIMMWaveControlCfg.dfeDataOutputMode != MMWave_DFEDataOutputMode_FRAME) &&
577  (gCLIMMWaveControlCfg.dfeDataOutputMode != MMWave_DFEDataOutputMode_ADVANCED_FRAME))
578  {
579  CLI_write ("Error: Configuration is valid only if the DFE Output Mode is Frame or Advanced Frame\n");
580  return -1;
581  }
582 
583  if (gCLIMMWaveControlCfg.dfeDataOutputMode == MMWave_DFEDataOutputMode_FRAME)
584  {
585  ptrBaseCfgProfileHandle = &gCLIMMWaveControlCfg.u.frameCfg.profileHandle[0U];
586  }
587  else
588  {
589  ptrBaseCfgProfileHandle = &gCLIMMWaveControlCfg.u.advancedFrameCfg.profileHandle[0U];
590  }
591 
592  /* Initialize the profile configuration: */
593  memset ((void *)&profileCfg, 0, sizeof(rlProfileCfg_t));
594 
595  /* Populate the profile configuration: */
596  profileCfg.profileId = atoi (argv[1]);
597 
598  /* Translate from GHz to [1 LSB = 3.6e9 / 2^26 Hz = 53.644 Hz] units of mmwavelink format */
599  profileCfg.startFreqConst = (uint32_t) (atof(argv[2]) * (1U << 26) / 3.6);
600 
601  /* Translate below times from us to [1 LSB = 10 ns] units of mmwavelink format */
602  profileCfg.idleTimeConst = (uint32_t)((float)atof(argv[3]) * 1000 / 10);
603  profileCfg.adcStartTimeConst = (uint32_t)((float)atof(argv[4]) * 1000 / 10);
604  profileCfg.rampEndTime = (uint32_t)((float)atof(argv[5]) * 1000 / 10);
605 
606  profileCfg.txOutPowerBackoffCode = atoi (argv[6]);
607  profileCfg.txPhaseShifter = atoi (argv[7]);
608 
609  /* Translate from MHz/us to [1 LSB = (3.6e6 * 900) / 2^26 = 48.279 kHz/uS] units of mmwavelink format */
610  profileCfg.freqSlopeConst = (int16_t)(atof(argv[8]) * (1U << 26) / (3.6e3 * 900.0));
611 
612  /* Translate from us to [1 LSB = 10 ns] units of mmwavelink format */
613  profileCfg.txStartTime = (int32_t)((float)atof(argv[9]) * 1000 / 10);
614 
615  profileCfg.numAdcSamples = atoi (argv[10]);
616  profileCfg.digOutSampleRate = atoi (argv[11]);
617  profileCfg.hpfCornerFreq1 = atoi (argv[12]);
618  profileCfg.hpfCornerFreq2 = atoi (argv[13]);
619  profileCfg.rxGain = atoi (argv[14]);
620  /* Currently setting this field to backwards compatible value. To set this field appropriately
621  * for different tx patterns please refer to the profileCfg api documentation
622  * For example the use case "BPM MIMO with 2 simultaneous antennas enabled" could benefit
623  * from enabling the calibration for 2 antennas by updating this field
624  */
625  profileCfg.txCalibEnCfg = 0U;
626 
627  /* Search for a free space in the mmWave configuration block: */
628  for (index = 0U; index < MMWAVE_MAX_PROFILE; index++)
629  {
630  /* Did we get a free entry? */
631  if (ptrBaseCfgProfileHandle[index] == NULL)
632  {
633  /* YES: We can add the profile. */
634  break;
635  }
636  }
637  if (index == MMWAVE_MAX_PROFILE)
638  {
639  /* Error: All the profiles have been exhausted */
640  return -1;
641  }
642 
643  /* Add the profile to the mmWave module: */
644  profileHandle = MMWave_addProfile (gCLI.cfg.mmWaveHandle, &profileCfg, &errCode);
645  if (profileHandle == NULL)
646  {
647  /* Error: Unable to add the profile. Return the error code back */
648  return errCode;
649  }
650 
651  /* Record the profile: */
652  ptrBaseCfgProfileHandle[index] = profileHandle;
653  return 0;
654 }

673 static int32_t CLI_MMWaveChirpCfg (int32_t argc, char* argv[])
674 {
675  rlChirpCfg_t chirpCfg;
676  MMWave_ProfileHandle profileHandle;
677  int32_t errCode;
678 
679  /* Sanity Check: Minimum argument check */
680  if (argc != 9)
681  {
682  CLI_write ("Error: Invalid usage of the CLI command\n");
683  return -1;
684  }
685 
686  /* Sanity Check: Chirp configuration is valid only for the Frame or
687  Advanced Frame Mode: */
688  if ((gCLIMMWaveControlCfg.dfeDataOutputMode != MMWave_DFEDataOutputMode_FRAME) &&
689  (gCLIMMWaveControlCfg.dfeDataOutputMode != MMWave_DFEDataOutputMode_ADVANCED_FRAME))
690  {
691  CLI_write ("Error: Configuration is valid only if the DFE Output Mode is Chirp\n");
692  return -1;
693  }
694 
695  /* Initialize the chirp configuration: */
696  memset ((void *)&chirpCfg, 0, sizeof(rlChirpCfg_t));
697 
698  /* Populate the chirp configuration: */
699  chirpCfg.chirpStartIdx = atoi (argv[1]);
700  chirpCfg.chirpEndIdx = atoi (argv[2]);
701  chirpCfg.profileId = atoi (argv[3]);
702 
703  /* Translate from Hz to number of [1 LSB = 3.6e9/2^26 = 53.644 Hz] units of mmwavelink format */
704  chirpCfg.startFreqVar = (uint32_t) ((float)atof(argv[4]) * (1U << 26) / 3.6e9);
705 
706  /* Translate from KHz/us to number of [1 LSB = 3.6e6 * 900/2^26 = 48.279 KHz/us] units of mmwavelink format */
707  chirpCfg.freqSlopeVar = (uint16_t) ((float)atof(argv[5]) * (1U << 26) / (3.6e6 * 900.0));
708 
709  /* Translate from us to [1 LSB = 10ns] units of mmwavelink format */
710  chirpCfg.idleTimeVar = (uint32_t)((float)atof (argv[6]) * 1000.0 / 10.0);
711 
712  /* Translate from us to [1 LSB = 10ns] units of mmwavelink format */
713  chirpCfg.adcStartTimeVar = (uint32_t)((float)atof (argv[7]) * 1000.0 / 10.0);
714 
715  chirpCfg.txEnable = atoi (argv[8]);
716 
717  /* Get the profile handle to which the chirp is to be added: */
718  if (MMWave_getProfileHandle (gCLI.cfg.mmWaveHandle, chirpCfg.profileId,
719  &profileHandle, &errCode) < 0)
720  {
721  /* Error: Unable to get the profile handle. Return the error code */
722  return errCode;
723  }
724 
725  /* Add the chirp to the profile */
726  if (MMWave_addChirp (profileHandle, &chirpCfg, &errCode) == NULL)
727  {
728  /* Error: Unable to add the chirp. Return the error code. */
729  return errCode;
730  }
731  return 0;
732 }

751 static int32_t CLI_MMWaveFrameCfg (int32_t argc, char* argv[])
752 {
753  rlFrameCfg_t frameCfg;
754 
755  /* Sanity Check: Minimum argument check */

1089 int32_t CLI_MMWaveExtensionHandler(int32_t argc, char* argv[])
1090 {
1091  CLI_CmdTableEntry* ptrCLICommandEntry;
1092  int32_t cliStatus;
1093  int32_t retVal = 0;
1094 
1095  /* Get the pointer to the mmWave extension table */
1096  ptrCLICommandEntry = &gCLIMMWaveExtensionTable[0];
1097 
1098  /* Cycle through all the registered externsion CLI commands: */
1099  while (ptrCLICommandEntry->cmdHandlerFxn != NULL)
1100  {
1101  /* Do we have a match? */
1102  if (strcmp(ptrCLICommandEntry->cmd, argv[0]) == 0)
1103  {
1104  /* YES: Pass this to the CLI registered function */
1105  cliStatus = ptrCLICommandEntry->cmdHandlerFxn (argc, argv);
1106  if (cliStatus == 0)
1107  {
1108  /* Successfully executed the CLI command: */
1109  CLI_write ("Done\n");
1110  }
1111  else
1112  {
1113  /* Error: The CLI command failed to execute */
1114  CLI_write ("Error %d\n", cliStatus);
1115  }
1116  break;
1117  }
1118 
1119  /* Get the next entry: */
1120  ptrCLICommandEntry++;
1121  }
1122 
1123  /* Was this a valid CLI command? */
1124  if (ptrCLICommandEntry->cmdHandlerFxn == NULL)
1125  {
1126  /* NO: The command was not a valid CLI mmWave extension command. Setup
1127  * the return value correctly. */
1128  retVal = -1;
1129  }
1130  return retVal;
1131 }
